ed-brewing-shore\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"SessionStart\",\"hookName\":\"SessionStart:clear\",\"command\":\"cmux claude-hook session-start\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"55dc5e08-44b2-4f2c-9848-3958590d247f\",\"toolUseID\":\"55dc5e08-44b2-4f2c-9848-3958590d247f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T19:40:01.206Z\",\"uuid\":\"0bb05328-f553-478a-bf14-860b3115421a\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"0bb05328-f553-478a-bf14-860b3115421a\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/factoryai-agent\",\"sessionId\":\"22266b86-af98-4794-a6a8-7c7287c079a1\",\"version\":\"2.1.49\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/factoryai-agent\",\"slug\":\"structured-brewing-shore\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"SessionStart\",\"hookName\":\"SessionStart:clear\",\"command\":\"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/hooks-handlers/session-start.sh\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"55dc5e08-44b2-4f2c-9848-3958590d247f\",\"toolUseID\":\"55dc5e08-44b2-4f2c-9848-3958590d247f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T19:40:01.206Z\",\"uuid\":\"510005f7-0891-4591-af2b-8ea2d5b98d2d\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"510005f7-0891-4591-af2b-8ea2d5b98d2d\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/factoryai-agent\",\"sessionId\":\"22266b86-af98-4794-a6a8-7c7287c079a1\",\"version\":\"2.1.49\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/factoryai-agent\",\"slug\":\"structured-brewing-shore\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Fix Droid \\\"(no prompt)\\\" after commit\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nWhen a Factory AI Droid session creates checkpoints and the user commits, `entire explain` shows `(no prompt)` for the committed checkpoint. Before the commit, the temporary (shadow branch) checkpoint correctly shows the prompt.\\n\\n**Root cause**: Three functions parse transcripts in an agent-aware way (Gemini vs Claude Code) but lack a Droid-specific path. Since Droid uses a different JSONL envelope (`{\\\"type\\\":\\\"message\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"role\\\":\\\"user\\\",...}}`) vs Claude Code (`{\\\"type\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"content\\\":...}}`), the generic Claude Code parser fails to find user messages. The top-level `type` is always `\\\"message\\\"`, which doesn't match the `\\\"user\\\"`/`\\\"human\\\"` check.\\n\\nTemporary checkpoints work because `SaveStep()` uses the agent-specific `ExtractPrompts()` method (in `lifecycle.go`) which correctly handles the Droid envelope. Committed checkpoints fail because condensation re-extracts prompts from the raw transcript using the generic parser.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. Add Droid handling to `extractUserPrompts()`\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go:500-527`\\n\\nAdd a `case agent.AgentTypeFactoryAIDroid` branch that uses `factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes()` to normalize the transcript, then extracts user messages from the normalized lines using `transcript.ExtractUserContent()`.\\n\\n```go\\nfunc extractUserPrompts(agentType agent.AgentType, content string) []string {\\n    if content == \\\"\\\" {\\n        return nil\\n    }\\n\\n    // Droid has its own envelope format — use its parser\\n    if agentType == agent.AgentTypeFactoryAIDroid {\\n        lines, err := factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes([]byte(content))\\n        if err != nil {\\n            return nil\\n        }\\n        var prompts []string\\n        for _, line := range lines {\\n            if line.Type != transcript.TypeUser {\\n                continue\\n            }\\n            if text := transcript.ExtractUserContent(line.Message); text != \\\"\\\" {\\n                if stripped := textutil.StripIDEContextTags(text); stripped != \\\"\\\" {\\n                    prompts = append(prompts, stripped)\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return prompts\\n    }\\n\\n    // (existing Gemini + Claude Code logic unchanged)\\n    ...\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 2. Add Droid handling to `calculateTokenUsage()`\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go:533-562`\\n\\nAdd a `case agent.AgentTypeFactoryAIDroid` branch that uses `factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes()` + `factoryaidroid.CalculateTokenUsage()`.\\n\\n```go\\nfunc calculateTokenUsage(agentType agent.AgentType, data []byte, startOffset int) *agent.TokenUsage {\\n    ...\\n    // Droid has its own envelope format — use its parser\\n    if agentType == agent.AgentTypeFactoryAIDroid {\\n        lines, err := factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes(data)\\n        if err != nil || len(lines) == 0 {\\n            return &agent.TokenUsage{}\\n        }\\n        if startOffset > 0 && startOffset < len(lines) {\\n            lines = lines[startOffset:]\\n        }\\n        return factoryaidroid.CalculateTokenUsage(lines)\\n    }\\n    ...\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 3. Add Droid handling to `BuildCondensedTranscriptFromBytes()`\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/summarize/summarize.go:115-128`\\n\\nThe function already groups `AgentTypeFactoryAIDroid` with Claude Code (line 119), but then uses `transcript.ParseFromBytes()` which doesn't normalize the Droid envelope. Fix: use `factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes()` for Droid, then pass normalized lines to `BuildCondensedTranscript()`.\\n\\n```go\\nfunc BuildCondensedTranscriptFromBytes(content []byte, agentType agent.AgentType) ([]Entry, error) {\\n    switch agentType {\\n    case agent.AgentTypeGemini:\\n        return buildCondensedTranscriptFromGemini(content)\\n    case agent.AgentTypeFactoryAIDroid:\\n        lines, err := factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes(content)\\n        if err != nil {\\n            return nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to parse Droid transcript: %w\\\", err)\\n        }\\n        return BuildCondensedTranscript(lines), nil\\n    case agent.AgentTypeClaudeCode, agent.AgentTypeUnknown:\\n        // Claude format - fall through to shared logic below\\n    }\\n    lines, err := transcript.ParseFromBytes(content)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to parse transcript: %w\\\", err)\\n    }\\n    return BuildCondensedTranscript(lines), nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 4. Add import for `factoryaidroid` package\\n**Files**:\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` - add `\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid\\\"`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/summarize/summarize.go` - add `\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid\\\"`\\n\\nBoth files already import other agent packages (`claudecode`, `geminicli`), so this is consistent.\\n\\n## Existing code to reuse\\n\\n- `factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes()` — `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/transcript.go:50` — normalizes Droid JSONL to `transcript.Line` (already exists, tested)\\n- `factoryaidroid.CalculateTokenUsage()` — `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/transcript.go:171` — computes token usage from normalized lines (already exists, handles streaming dedup)\\n- `transcript.ExtractUserContent()` — `cmd/entire/cli/transcript/parse.go` — extracts text from normalized message (already used by Droid's `ExtractPrompts()`)\\n- `textutil.StripIDEContextTags()` — strips IDE context tags (already used everywhere)\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci` — all tests pass, no lint errors\\n2. Manual test: run a Droid session, create a checkpoint, commit, then `entire explain` — prompt should now appear\\n3. Existing integration tests should continue to pass (no behavioral change for Claude Code or Gemini)\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alisha/.REDACTED.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"2640f024-22c7-4115-b8cf-23825f0ff4ea\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T19:40:00.788Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Fix Droid \\\"(no prompt)\\\" after commit\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nWhen a Factory AI Droid session creates checkpoints and the user commits, `entire explain` shows `(no prompt)` for the committed checkpoint. Before the commit, the temporary (shadow branch) checkpoint correctly shows the prompt.\\n\\n**Root cause**: Three functions parse transcripts in an agent-aware way (Gemini vs Claude Code) but lack a Droid-specific path. Since Droid uses a different JSONL envelope (`{\\\"type\\\":\\\"message\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"role\\\":\\\"user\\\",...}}`) vs Claude Code (`{\\\"type\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"content\\\":...}}`), the generic Claude Code parser fails to find user messages. The top-level `type` is always `\\\"message\\\"`, which doesn't match the `\\\"user\\\"`/`\\\"human\\\"` check.\\n\\nTemporary checkpoints work because `SaveStep()` uses the agent-specific `ExtractPrompts()` method (in `lifecycle.go`) which correctly handles the Droid envelope. Committed checkpoints fail because condensation re-extracts prompts from the raw transcript using the generic parser.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. Add Droid handling to `extractUserPrompts()`\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go:500-527`\\n\\nAdd a `case agent.AgentTypeFactoryAIDroid` branch that uses `factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes()` to normalize the transcript, then extracts user messages from the normalized lines using `transcript.ExtractUserContent()`.\\n\\n```go\\nfunc extractUserPrompts(agentType agent.AgentType, content string) []string {\\n    if content == \\\"\\\" {\\n        return nil\\n    }\\n\\n    // Droid has its own envelope format — use its parser\\n    if agentType == agent.AgentTypeFactoryAIDroid {\\n        lines, err := factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes([]byte(content))\\n        if err != nil {\\n            return nil\\n        }\\n        var prompts []string\\n        for _, line := range lines {\\n            if line.Type != transcript.TypeUser {\\n                continue\\n            }\\n            if text := transcript.ExtractUserContent(line.Message); text != \\\"\\\" {\\n                if stripped := textutil.StripIDEContextTags(text); stripped != \\\"\\\" {\\n                    prompts = append(prompts, stripped)\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return prompts\\n    }\\n\\n    // (existing Gemini + Claude Code logic unchanged)\\n    ...\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 2. Add Droid handling to `calculateTokenUsage()`\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go:533-562`\\n\\nAdd a `case agent.AgentTypeFactoryAIDroid` branch that uses `factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes()` + `factoryaidroid.CalculateTokenUsage()`.\\n\\n```go\\nfunc calculateTokenUsage(agentType agent.AgentType, data []byte, startOffset int) *agent.TokenUsage {\\n    ...\\n    // Droid has its own envelope format — use its parser\\n    if agentType == agent.AgentTypeFactoryAIDroid {\\n        lines, err := factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes(data)\\n        if err != nil || len(lines) == 0 {\\n            return &agent.TokenUsage{}\\n        }\\n        if startOffset > 0 && startOffset < len(lines) {\\n            lines = lines[startOffset:]\\n        }\\n        return factoryaidroid.CalculateTokenUsage(lines)\\n    }\\n    ...\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 3. Add Droid handling to `BuildCondensedTranscriptFromBytes()`\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/summarize/summarize.go:115-128`\\n\\nThe function already groups `AgentTypeFactoryAIDroid` with Claude Code (line 119), but then uses `transcript.ParseFromBytes()` which doesn't normalize the Droid envelope. Fix: use `factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes()` for Droid, then pass normalized lines to `BuildCondensedTranscript()`.\\n\\n```go\\nfunc BuildCondensedTranscriptFromBytes(content []byte, agentType agent.AgentType) ([]Entry, error) {\\n    switch agentType {\\n    case agent.AgentTypeGemini:\\n        return buildCondensedTranscriptFromGemini(content)\\n    case agent.AgentTypeFactoryAIDroid:\\n        lines, err := factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes(content)\\n        if err != nil {\\n            return nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to parse Droid transcript: %w\\\", err)\\n        }\\n        return BuildCondensedTranscript(lines), nil\\n    case agent.AgentTypeClaudeCode, agent.AgentTypeUnknown:\\n        // Claude format - fall through to shared logic below\\n    }\\n    lines, err := transcript.ParseFromBytes(content)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to parse transcript: %w\\\", err)\\n    }\\n    return BuildCondensedTranscript(lines), nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 4. Add import for `factoryaidroid` package\\n**Files**:\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` - add `\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid\\\"`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/summarize/summarize.go` - add `\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid\\\"`\\n\\nBoth files already import other agent packages (`claudecode`, `geminicli`), so this is consistent.\\n\\n## Existing code to reuse\\n\\n- `factoryaidroid.ParseDroidTranscriptFromBytes()` — `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/transcript.go:50` — normalizes Droid JSONL to `transcript.Line` (already exists, tested)\\n- `factoryaidroid.CalculateTokenUsage()` — `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/transcript.go:171` — computes token usage from normalized lines (already exists, handles streaming dedup)\\n- `transcript.ExtractUserContent()` — `cmd/entire/cli/transcript/parse.go` — extracts text from normalized message (already used by Droid's `ExtractPrompts()`)\\n- `textutil.StripIDEContextTags()` — strips IDE context tags (already used everywhere)\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci` — all tests pass, no lint errors\\n2. Manual test: run a Droid session, create a checkpoint, commit, then `entire explain` — prompt should now appear\\n3. Existing integration tests should continue to pass (no behavioral change for Claude Code or Gemini)\\n\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"2640f024-22c7-4115-b8cf-23825f0ff4ea\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/factoryai-agent\",\"sessionId\":\"22266b86-af98-4794-a6a8-7c7287c079a1\",\"version\":\"2.1.49\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/factoryai-agent\",\"slug\":\"structured-brewing-shore\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_011CQsDXgydXUrAi4EsLfasN\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n\\n`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\\nThis is a classic \\\"dual parsing path\\\" bug: the agent-specific parser is used for live checkpoints but the generic parser is used during condensation (commit-time). The fix ensures all three condensation functions route through the Droid-specific parser, just like the live checkpoint path already does.\\n`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`\\n\\nLet me start by reading the three files I need to modify to understand the current code.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":10213,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":23059,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":10213},\"output_tokens\":2,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYKtV2MUq92a9KZjUhYG3\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"6d46aea1-3bb1-46cf-a9ca-6422aa2051f3\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T19:40:07.095Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"6d46aea1-3bb1-46cf-a9ca-6422aa2051f3\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/factoryai-agent\",\"sessionId\":\"22266b86-af98-4794-a6a8-7c7287c079a1\",\"version\":\"2.1.49\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/factoryai-agent\",\"slug\":\"structured-brewing-shore\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_011CQsDXgydXUrAi4EsLfasN\",\"type\":\"message\",\"ro